    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9b1127f1_7106618f",
        "filename": "tools/skpbench/skpbench.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 83,
      "author": {
        "id": 5633
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-29T15:04:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Do we ever use these methods?\n\nThe output is designed to report the min, max, median, etc. of 1 single value, and the \"clock\" field currently tells us whether these times should be understood as \"cpu\" or \"gpu\".\n\nDo you think instead we could add a third clock called \"ddl\"? We would need another command line flag, and then the ddl Benchmark could decide on its own whether to record \"cpu\" times (i.e. total frame times as recorded by the CPU, using a gpuSync) into fDuration, or \"ddl\" times (i.e. just the ddl record times.). When printing the output, we would write \"ddl\" to the clock field if the values are to be understood as just the ddl Record Times.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 78,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 83,
        "endChar": 75
      },
      "revId": "6c623b9ed9d3a6b74df2627eb03bb25211c8a94a",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e33825aa_720bc2e6",
        "filename": "tools/skpbench/skpbench.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 83,
      "author": {
        "id": 5230
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-29T18:34:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We don\u0027t use them yet.\n\nI have yet to talk w/ Joe about this but I suspect that, to get perf to behave how I want, I will need to run the skpbench ddl bots twice. Once to spit out the combined time and once to spit out only the ddl record time.",
      "parentUuid": "9b1127f1_7106618f",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 78,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 83,
        "endChar": 75
      },
      "revId": "6c623b9ed9d3a6b74df2627eb03bb25211c8a94a",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7d45f230_b7ce9dde",
        "filename": "tools/skpbench/skpbench.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 13
      },
      "lineNbr": 83,
      "author": {
        "id": 5633
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-29T19:07:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Agreed.\n\nSo how would you feel about instead, just not including ddl record timings for this CL? In a future one we can add a new command line flag for a \"ddl-record\" clock where we use the normal fDuration field in the sample to store the record times, and a second bot invocation can use it?",
      "parentUuid": "e33825aa_720bc2e6",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 78,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 83,
        "endChar": 75
      },
      "revId": "6c623b9ed9d3a6b74df2627eb03bb25211c8a94a",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
